result.execSummary:
The defendant James I. Cross was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Identity Theft - Obtain Money or Credit [Modifiers: Conspiracy to Commit, Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.203(2)(a).
  • Fraudulent Claim/Income Tax Credit [Modifiers: Conspiracy to Commit, Repeater], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 71.83(2)(b)4.
  • Theft-False Representation >$10,000 [Modifiers: Party to a Crime, Repeater], a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(d).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Case set for sentencing hearing. Judge is ill and unable to hear this matter today. Parties do not object to an adjournment. Defendant James I. Cross in court with attorney Jeffrey J Guerard.  Defendant James I. Cross in custody.  
Kurt Brian Benkley appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  
Deputy Court Clerk: dds.

Defendant prepared to enter change of plea.  Hearing proceeded.  Negotiations set forth by the state.

AS TO COUNTS 1, 2, AND 3:  The defendant was advised of his constitutional rights and maximum penalties, waived all rights, plead GUILTY and was sworn and examined as to the plea.  Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights, Addendum to Plea Questionnaire, and Jury Instructions received and filed.  The parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis for the plea.  The Court found the defendant guilty and ordered entry of Judgment of Conviction.  Pursuant to Wisconsin Statutes Section 973.176, the Court advised the defendant of the following restrictions:  Firearm possession and Voting.  

AS TO COUNTS 13-18, AND 23:  Pursuant to plea negotiations and on state's motion the Court orders the aforementioned counts DISMISSED AND READ-IN for the purpose of sentencing.

The Court orders the defendant REMANDED into custody at this time.  Parties advised effective August 3, 2015, this case will be reassigned to Judge Rothstein, Branch 25, Room G55A of the Criminal Justice Facility.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for August 21, 2015 at 08:30 am.
